<title>UK: RESEARCH ALERT- Merrill raises Pilkington.</title>
<headline>RESEARCH ALERT- Merrill raises Pilkington.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1996-10-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Glassmaker Pilkington Plc was raised to &quot;accumulate&quot; from &quot;neutral&quot; at Merrill Lynch even as the broking house trimmed its earnings estimates for the company, market sources said on Tuesday.  </p>
<p>Traders said Merrill cut its earnings per share estimates for fiscal 1997 and 1998 by some 10.5 percent to 14.0p and 10.8p respectively, citing weak European prices and current Australian trading conditions.</p>
<p>Analysts at the brokerage were not immediately available for comment. The stock was down 1/2p at 189.</p>
<p>-- David Holmes, London Newsroom +44 171 542 5106</p>
